-- Mizuho Close to Setting Volume Record in Tokyo After Share Lockup Ends
-- Akiko Ikeda
-- 2010-07-22T05:55:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/mizuho-close-to-setting-volume-record-in-tokyo-after-share-lockup-ends.html

          
          
             Mizuho Financial Group Inc. , Japanâ€™s
second-largest publicly traded bank by assets, is close to
setting a record for the number of shares traded on the Tokyo
Stock Exchange.  
 More than 930 million shares changed hands as of 2:53 p.m.
local time, nearing the 1.04 billion shares of Japan Airlines
Corp. exchanged on Jan. 14, according to the bourse.  
 Today is the first day that investors can sell the shares
they bought in a public offering this month.  
